# No deferrals without explicit operator word

**Default: finish it.** If the operator asked for a complete outcome (e.g. "replace React with Rust", "do the whole plan"), **ship the whole outcome**. Do not invent deferrals.

## The only legal deferral

The operator **explicitly** says, in this conversation (or a quoted prior message they reaffirm), words like:

- "defer X"
- "skip X"
- "not this pass — X later"
- "MVP only — leave Y"

**Quote that authorization** in the verify log / commit body. No quote → **not deferred**.

Soft plan prose ("if feasible", "optional", "P1 later", "fold forward", "record as follow-up") is **not** authorization — including when **you** wrote that prose into the plan.

## Forbidden (these are failures, not process)

```text
❌ "Folded forward" / "deferred to T-xxx" / "follow-on" for in-scope work
❌ Shipping an MVP and calling the program/slice "complete" while listed scope remains
❌ Writing your own "Out of scope" / "Deferred" section to shrink an operator "do everything" ask
❌ "Document as deferred" in a verify log instead of implementing
❌ Partial ship + "operator can do the rest later" without explicit defer approval
❌ Treating audit P0/P1 labels as permission to skip P1 when the ask was complete cutover
```

```text
✅ Implement every item required by the operator ask / approved plan Scope / acceptance matrix
✅ If truly blocked (secrets, Workbench down, missing GPU): STOP and ASK — do not invent a deferral ticket and mark done
✅ Defer only after operator: "defer satellite" / "skip Smart Forge this pass"
```

## Plans and audits

When drafting a finish plan: **do not pre-load deferrals**. List remaining work as **must-do**. If something might need operator judgment, **ask before** writing "fold forward" into the plan. A plan that ships with a Deferred appendix the operator never approved is non-compliant.

## Cursor Mode B / Claude handoffs

- Do **not** put "fold forward X" / "out of scope: do Y later" in specs/handoffs unless the operator already authorized that deferral.
- `═══ DO NOT ═══` may ban unrelated lanes; it must **not** silently drop the operator's complete-outcome ask.

## Interaction with Mode A/B/C

Does **not** authorize Cursor to write app code. It binds **every** agent (Cursor, Claude Code, Fable, auditors): no silent or self-authored deferrals.
